article.description: Jalin Hart had a career-high 28 points as Incarnate Word held off Division II St. Edward's 93-90 to win its 10th straight home opener on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Harts leads Incarnate Word to 93-90 win over St. Edward's
article.linkText: Harts leads Incarnate Word to 93-90 win over St. Edward's
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Jalin Hart had a career-high 28 points as Incarnate Word held off Division II St. Edward's 93-90 to win its 10th straight home opener on Tuesday night. Incarnate Word (1-1) led for most of the second period but Sean Watkins nailed a 3-pointer as St. Edwards closed the gap to 92-90 with 20 seconds left. Hart was fouled on the next play and split a pair of free throws for the final score. Hart hit 3 of 7 from beyond the arc and was 11 of 17 from the floor. Shawn Johnson added 19 points and pulled down 11 rebounds. The score was tied at 42 at the break. James Taylor nailed a 3 and the Hilltoppers scored the first five points of the second half. The Cardinals took the lead for good with 9:51 remaining but never led by more than five points. Ramir Burton led St. Edward's with 23 points.
